  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IProcessorWithTargetName, ITargetProcessorSubmitIssues, ICLIOptionDefinitionProvider, IProcessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ADOTargetProcessorSubmitIssues, ArcherTargetProcessorSubmitIssues, JiraTargetProcessorSubmitIssues, OctaneTargetProcessorSubmitIssues

    public abstract class AbstractTargetProcessorSubmitIssues
extends AbstractTargetProcessor
implements ITargetProcessorSubmitIssues
    This abstract IProcessor implementation allows for submitting issues to external systems based on vulnerability data. Based on our superclass AbstractProcessorBuildObjectMapFromGroupedObjects, we build a map containing issue information to be submitted from (optionally grouped) vulnerability data. Actual implementations will need to implement the submitIssue(Context, LinkedHashMap) method to actually submit the issue to the external system.
    Author:
    Ruud Senden

      • isIgnorePreviouslySubmittedIssues

        public boolean isIgnorePreviouslySubmittedIssues()
        Subclasses can override this method to re-submit any previously submitted issues, for example when exporting all vulnerabilities to a file. The default implementation returns true, indicating that previously submitted issues should be ignored.
